ASABA – Tragedy struck in Sapele community, Sapele Local Government Area after a 15-year-old boy committed suicide. SATURDAY INDEPENDENT gathered that the deceased, who was identified as Wisdom Tarbuka, lived with his guardian at New Ogorode Road, Sapele, where he allegedly drank Sniper, a popular insecticide and miticide containing the active ingredient Bifenthrin. It was learnt that the deceased was confirmed dead in the late hours of Friday, January 16, 2020 after he failed to wake up from his sleep. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! It was gathered that a bottle of Sniper was found close to the body of the deceased. A source, who identified as Bridget Aluka described the late boy has a lively child who they never thought could take his own life. Professor Waziri Appointed VC Federal University Gashua In Yobe APC Congratulates Bisi Akande On 82nd Birthday This incident comes two days after a Keke rider identified as Kevwe committed suicide after he drank a bottle of Sniper in Sapele community. At the time of filing this report, all efforts to reach Police Public Relation Officer (PPRO), DSP Onome Onovwakpoyeya, via phone calls and messages proved abortive.